Type: Package
Package: MRSimilarity
Title: Using Q-statistics to identify significant difference in mulitple causal estimates from Mendelian Randomisation (MR) methods
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Matthew Tyler, Ninon Mounier, Jack Bowden, Frank Dudbridge, Siyang Cai
Maintainer: Frank Dudbridge <frank.dudbridge@leicester.ac.uk>, Siyang Cai
    <sc814@leicester.ac.uk>
Description: This package aims to assessing the similarity of an arbitrary set of MR estimates whilst accounting for their correlation. A generalisation of the Q statistic is applied for multivariate normal data. Users are recommended to perform multiple testing when overall hypothesis is found significant. Scatter plot of causal estimates and IV assumption tests statistics are included.
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/SiyangCai/MRSimilarity
BugReports: https://github.com/SiyangCai/MRSimilarity/issues/
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5)
Imports: 
    plotly,
    PBSmodelling,
    gtools,
    summarytools,
Remotes:
    MRCIEU/TwoSampleMR
Encoding: UTF-8
